    "long_description": "Rajput Miniature painting evolved in the royal courts of Rajasthan during the 16th to 19th centuries. It is known for its intricate detailing, vibrant colors (often derived from semi-precious stones), and themes revolving around the life of royalty, mythology (Krishna-Radha), and nature.\n\nDifferent schools emerged in different kingdoms: \n- **Mewar**: Bold colors.\n- **Bundi/Kota**: Hunting scenes and lush vegetation.\n- **Kishangarh**: Highly stylized features (Bani Thani).\n- **Jaipur**: Mughal influence.",
